0 Your hero has a number of abilities that affect his achievements and his army's effectiveness. 
0 A hero's experience grows when he wins battles and completes quests. As you reach a higher level, however, the experience drops back to 0, and you have to start amassing new one. 
0 There are four basic abilities that vary from race to race; they can be increased as your hero reaches higher levels. 
0 The abilities of your hero are given talents, his inborn gifts that will naturally influence his success in the game. The skills of your hero, on the other hand, are functions of his abilities. A skill is a practical expertise that can be increased either by developing appropriate abilities (or redistributing stats between them) or by wearing a relevant item.
0 Mana denotes the level of your skill in magic.
0 Attack is the skill--and power--with which you assault your enemies.
0 Defence indicates the level of resistance of your army against attack; the higher your defence skill is, the harder it is to destroy your troops.
0 Trade is the skill with which you make business transactions. Each game day you receive 100 coins for each stat you have in this skill.
0 Leadership is an important skill that determines the maximum number of warriors you can have in your army.
0 First Strike is the skill that increases your chances to attack first in battle.
